National Treasury published the special adjustment budget guidelines on its website which include the budget process to be followed.

The special budget follows President Cyril Ramaphosa’s announcement that government would provide $27 billion in fiscal support to deal with COVID-19.

Economist Iraj Abedian says,"It was inevitable. As we all know the President has made a lot of announcement and Treasury to make this legal the National Treasury will have to resubmit a new budget to the parliament and get approval for this type of reallocations of fiscal spending."

The COVID-19 Social Relief of Distress grant will benefit individuals who are currently unemployed and do not receive any other form of social grant or Unemployment Insurance Fund-payment.  
--SABC--